eins from his horse, and wasn't sure if Romo was running away or lying on the ground when Canales shot him. The trial is scheduled to run through the week.\par \par \uc2 Document TUCS000020140722ea7m0000l\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 News\par {\*\bkmkstart toc41}{\*\bkmkend toc41}\b \uc2 6 in GOPgovernorrace stressthe border ; In debate, they saysecuring it is tiedto Ariz. economy\b0\par\par\uc2 Howard Fischer   \par \uc2 Howard Fischer Capitol Media Services\par \uc2 1,010 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 July 2014\par \uc2 The Arizona Daily Star\par \uc2 TUCS\par A01\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 \u169\'00\'A9 2014 The Arizona Daily Star. Provided by ProQuest Information and Learning. All Rights Reserved.   \par \par \uc2 PHOENIX -- The questions were about improving Arizona's economy.\par \par \uc2 But the answers provided during a televised debate Monday night by several Republican gubernatorial hopefuls were about securing the border, insisting the issues are linked. And some want to spend state tax dollars to do it.\par \par \uc2 Andrew Thomas\uc2  cited a \uc2 Center for Immigration Studies\uc2  report that said all new jobs created since 2000 "have been taken by immigrants, legal and illegal." The former Maricopa County Attorney said to fix high unemployment, "start with the obvious."\par \par \uc2 Former GoDaddy executive Christine Jones wants to spend money to send the National Guard to the border and construct additional miles of fence. She insists Arizona can simply send the bill for all that to \uc2 Congress\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 State Treasurer Doug Ducey said everything would be on the table. He said that includes "reprioritizing" the $300 million budget of the state Department of Public Safety and working with local sheriffs to focus on illegal immigration.\par \par \uc2 Secretary of State \uc2 Ken Bennett\uc2  chided Jones, pointing out that Arizona has sent invoices to Washington before for things like paying the costs of incarcerating illegal immigrants who violate 